From c0fd3a4801be07ee6536411fa5a90f754ea21c87 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vincenzo@igrimaldi.engineering>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 12:37:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(demo): live robot cell on /demo instead of static 3D box

Replace the static PalletVisualizer3D on the Live Optimizer with the existing
animated cell (Scene/PalletizerArm/Conveyor) that already drives the Robot
Execution demo. The arm builds the generated plan pick-by-pick: conveyor feeds
the real upcoming cartons, the gripper follows the same 2-link IK to each
placement's exact optimizer coordinates, boxes land via visibleCount.

- Reuses proven components; no new arm, no engine change.
- Same RAF pacing + Run/Pause/Reset/speed controls as the robot demo.
- Auto-runs the build when a plan is generated.

Typecheck clean; parity PASS. Visual pass still needed in a browser (3D not
render-verifiable in CI).
